Document: WebRTCDataChannelExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_webrtcdatachannelextension.rst
Summary: Base class for custom WebRTC DataChannel implementations.

Inherits: Object < WebRTCDataChannelExtension

This class is a base for custom WebRTC DataChannel implementations. It is not intended to be used directly. Instead, you should extend this class and implement the virtual methods to create your own DataChannel.

The WebRTCDataChannelExtension class provides a way to extend the functionality of the built-in WebRTC DataChannel. This is useful for scenarios where you need to implement custom behavior for sending and receiving data over a WebRTC connection.

To create a custom DataChannel, you would typically:

1.  Create a new script that inherits from WebRTCDataChannelExtension.
2.  Implement the virtual methods such as _on_data_received, _on_state_changed, and _send_data.
3.  Register your custom DataChannel with the WebRTC connection.

This allows for advanced use cases such as custom serialization, encryption, or specialized data handling protocols on top of the standard WebRTC DataChannel.
